fields.description:
When changing the instance subdomain via modify-property the CC does not pick up the change and continues to use "eucalyptus.internal" as the search path:
{code}
# automatically generated config file for DHCP server
default-lease-time 86400;
max-lease-time 86400;
ddns-update-style none;

shared-network euca {
subnet 192.168.118.64 netmask 255.255.255.192 {
  option subnet-mask 255.255.255.192;
  option broadcast-address 192.168.118.127;
  option domain-name "eucalyptus.internal";
  option domain-name-servers 10.0.1.91, 10.0.1.1;
  option routers 192.168.118.66;
}

host node-192.168.118.107 {
  hardware ethernet D0:0D:08:6C:43:31;
  fixed-address 192.168.118.107;
}
}
{code}
{code}
[root@clcfrontend ~]# euca-describe-properties | grep domain
PROPERTY        cloud.vmstate.instance_subdomain        .cloud
PROPERTY        loadbalancing.loadbalancer_dns_subdomain        lb
PROPERTY        system.dns.dnsdomain    home
[root@clcfrontend ~]#
{code}

comments.body:
[~spark], I'm done with implementing this change. Can you do a quick sanity check of the changes. Basically these changes allow the CLC to push the "cloud.vmstate.instance_subdomain" property value to the CC (removing the first "." character) so the CC can update the euca-dhcp.conf file. The default value of the property is ".eucalyptus" which translate to "eucalyptus.internal" in the DHCP configuration file on CC. If you change it to ".cool.euca", the CC will update the configuration file with "cool.euca.internal".

