[~spark], one more change. I noticed that the DHCP config only update when the CC is restarted or a new instance is launched. For the currently running instance to pick the change in the absence of the previous 2 events, I check if the DescribeNetwork (subdomain and nameservers) have changed, and if this is the case, I basically kick the DHCP task to update the configuration during the "maintain network state" operation:

